  "text": "Empirical studies have shown that quantitative easing has accelerated the flow of capital into less economically developed countries beyond reasonable bounds [CITATION_1] . From within the Keynesian paradigm, quantitative easing was criticized on the grounds that with long-term bonds removed from their portfolios, investors would spend too much in other areas, which could lead to the overvaluation of certain assets and the associated bubble behavior [CITATION_2] ).",
